{
  "text": "Newborn screening for PKU meets all accepted screening criteria including cost-benefi t ratio. [CITATION_1] Therefore, newborn screening for PKU should be done in every European country. This screening not only needs a robust infrastructure in which blood is taken from all newborn babies within a few days of birth, but also a well equipped laboratory that can manage and assess bloodspots effi ciently. Low-income countries might consider using newborn screening laboratory facilities of another country as a possible option.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17952483"
